node.text:
3 cups chopped pineapple, plus 1 cup for garnish
1 large cucumber, peeled, seeded and chopped
1 1/2 cup pineapple juice
2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
2 tablespoons lime juice
1 jalapeño pepper, halved and seeded
3/4 tablespoon kosher salt
3 green onions, thinly sliced
2 tablespoons roughly chopped macadamia nuts, for garnish (optional)
2 tablespoons torn cilantro leaves, for garnish (optional) 
1/2 pound cooked shrimp, peeled and deveined (optional)

1. combine pineapple, cucumber, pineapple juice, oil, lime juice, jalapeño and salt in a blender and purée until smooth
2. add green onions and purée just until combined. transfer soup to a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours
3. in a small bowl, combine shrimp, pineapple, macadamia nuts and cilantro.
4. ladle soup into bowls and garnish with shrimp mixture

node.text:
everything you love about tacos except a lot easier: all you need is one pan, 20 minutes, zero tortilla rolling, and something to sip on — like maybe a margarita or threee!🍹💃🏼

{continue watching to see me gracefully spill sauce all over my yellow dress 💁🏼‍♀️}

simply toss tortilla strips in a pan (almond, corn, or flour tortillas work — go with tour fave!) cover with enchilada sauce, salsa, shredded chicken, and cheese; cook stovetop until nice and melty, and serve garnished with guac. enjoy!! 🍹

ONE PAN CHEESY CHICKEN TACO SKILLET
(gluten-free • grain-free • serves 4)

2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken • 1/2 tsp ground cumin • 1/2 tsp dried oregano • 1 cup red enchilada sauce • 1/2 cup chunky salsa • 1/4 cup water • 4 @sietefoods almond flour tortillas, cut into 1-inch strips • 1 cup shredded mexican cheese  blend cheese • 1/2 cup greek yogurt or sour cream • 1/4 cup sliced green onions • 1/4 cup chopped cilantro • guacamole • 

1) In large skillet add chicken and sprinkle with cumin and oregano. 2) add enchilada sauce, salsa, and water; bring to a simmer over medium heat for a couple of minutes to let sauce thicken. 3) stir in tortilla strips and sprinkle with cheese; remove from heat and and cover until cheese melts.) 4) top with greek yogurt, guacamole, cilantro, and green onions

one of my forever goals is to decrease my carbon footprint while increasing the nutrient load in my meals, which is why I keep @drpraegers in my freezer as a meatless options that’s fast and flavorful. 👌🏻😌 they just launched their cauliflower burger, which is loaded with all the good stuff: 9 grams of plant-based protein, 6 different vegetables, and 9 grams of whole foods-sourced fiber. the burgers are also gluten-free, grain-free, and non-gmo! 

dr. praeger’s is donating a percentage of sales to an organization called farmers against hunger 🌾, which bridges the gap between the agriculture industry and hunger relief organizations. ♥️ combatting food insecurity is a huge passion of mine, which makes me love this launch that much more. 

click the link in my profile to check out the new cauliflower burger or find them in the freezer aisle at your local grocery store. use my code HAVEN5 for $5 off your order! #sponsored #drpraegerspartner

Feeling full-on fall cozying up to a big bowl of PUMPKIN CHILI! 🥰🎃 This one comes together in under 20 minutes, thanks to the instant pot (although a slow cooker or stove top can be used if you prefer), and is packed with warming spices, hearty vegetables, and silky pumpkin purée, which adds amazing full-bodied flavor and texture. 👌🏻Toppings: add your favorites! I went with cheddar cheese, greek yogurt, and cilantro — all optional, but all encouraged. 👏🏻 
-
I also used @purefarmland plant-based protein starters and @betterthanbouillon organic seasoned vegetable base in this recipe — 100% plant-based products which have made it easy for me to incorporate more environmentally-friendly meals into my diet without sacrificing flavor ☺️🌍 🌱. Reducing my carbon footprint has been one of my goals this year and these products make it easier to do it 🧡. 
-
Be sure to check out the post on @purefarmland’s feed for the opportunity to enter an exciting giveaway —  you could have the chance to win $500 PLUS a variety of products from @purefarmland and @betterthanbouillon to recreate this chili recipe!Hope you enjoy it as much as we have! 😘
#PFfam #ad #betterthanbouillon
-
HEALTHY INSTANT POT PUMPKIN CHILI

1 T. olive oil
1 cup onion, chopped
1 green bell pepper, chopped
3 cloves garlic
1 pound Simply Seasoned Pure Farmland Protein Starter
1 (14oz) can diced tomatoes
1 (14oz) can pumpkin
1 (14oz) can kidney beans (drained)
1 (14oz) can white beans (drained)
2 T chili powder
1 tsp smoked paprika
1 tsp cumin
¼ tsp dried oregano
1 tsp Better Than Bouillon Seasoned Vegetable Base (dissolved in 8 oz boiling water) 

Optional Toppings:
Greek yogurt or sour cream, cilantro, grated cheese, avocado

1.In the saute mode,  cook onion, green pepper, and olive oil for 5 minutes.
2. Add garlic and Farmland Protein Starter. Break up with a spoon and saute 5 min.
3. Add all remaining ingredients to the instant pot. Cook on high pressure for 15 minutes before releasing pressure.

node.text: Long-term and sustainable change is usually the product of incremental changes. Navigating our roles — and assessing our impact — in the Black Lives Matter movement may feel overwhelming, but it doesn’t have to be. Making small, gradual changes will increase the likelihood that those changes are impactful and long-lasting.

Celebrating Cinco de Mayo with some sheet pan BBQ chicken zucchini chip nachooss 🌮. These have quickly become a quarantine happy hour staple — especially when served with a round of margs, which is definitely the move we’re making tonight! 🍹💃🏼
-
I like using equal parts tortilla chips and zucchini ‘chips,’ but if you’re looking to sneak in a couple extra veggie servings, go all parts zucchini! The beauty of nachos is that they’re totally customizable and can be topped with whatever you have on hand.
-
BBQ CHICKEN ZUCCHINI NACHOS 
1/2 bag tortilla chips (I usually use a grain-free cassava chip, but any works
2-3 zucchini, sliced 
Avocado or olive oil spray
1-2 cups shredded chicken breast 
1/2 cup @primalkitchenfoods Mango Jalapeño BBQ sauce (this *MAKES* the nachos)
1/2 cup pinto beans or black beans
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese 
1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, sliced
1/4 cup red onion, diced 
1/2 cup avocado, cubed 
1/4 cup sour cream or greek yogurt 
1/4 cup cilantro, chopped -
See IGTV video for directions! And bonus: use code SARA10 for a discount on your favorite Primal Kitchen products at primalkitchen.com 🎉🥳 My faves are their BBQ sauces, avocado oil mayos (they have a new pesto one that’s 👌🏻), and creamy dressings!

Pretty sure my quarantine diet is pushing 99% cookies, pizza, and banana bread at this point 🤣. Maintaining those ratios means baking multiple batches of these cookies (exhibit A: me yesterday) and ordering takeout 🍕 tonight (exhibit B: me counting down the hours till dinner). What are your weekend plans? I think these cookies should be apart of them 👏🏻. HAPPY FRIDAY! ❤️
-
FLOURLESS PEANUT BUTTER CHOCOLATE CHIP COOKIES

1 cup peanut butter 
3/4 cup coconut sugar, white sugar, or swerve granular (for low sugar/keto option)
1 egg
1/2 teaspoon baking soda 
1/4 teaspoon salt 
1 cup chocolate chips 
Preheat oven to 350 F. In a bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips. Stir to combine and then gently fold in chips. Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place in a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Dot with additional chocolate chips and bake ~10-12 minutes.

15 minute meatballsss! (plus some pasta + greens for good measure 👌🏻🍃🍝🤩). we’re all about fast + easy, especially when it’s cheesy, and these ITALIAN CHICKEN MEATBALLS are all of the above (and more!). meal prep at the beginning of the week for easy lunches and dinners later (pair with pasta or any savory side under the sun!). like those good good crispy edges? reheat in the air fryer for max yum .👌🏻

ITALIAN CHICKEN MEATBALLS
(gluten-free • grain-free • paleo-friendly)
1 lb. 90-93% lean ground chicken or turkey (note: you can sub 99% lean ground chicken breast, but the meatballs will be more dry and less juicy. Highly recommend going with 90-93% lean) + 2 garlic cloves, minced + 1/4 cup fresh parsley, finely chopped + 1.5 teaspoons onion powder + 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano + 1/4 teaspoon dried basil + 1/4 teaspoon sea salt 1/2 cup almond flour. combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix gently. using hands, roll into 1.5-inch balls and set aside. In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon olive oil or avocado oil over medium high heat; pan fry meatballs for approximately 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to brown all sides.

HERBY SPAGHETTI w/ GARLIC & PARMESAN: toss your favorite noodles (I used chickpea spaghetti) with a drizzle of olive oil, a dash of dried basil + dried oregano (or an italian herbs blend) and freshly grated parmesan cheese. 

SAUTÉED GARLICKY SPINACH: heat 1-2 teaspoons olive or avocado oil in a large skillet; add 2 cloves minced garlic and sauté a couple minutes; add 5-6 cups spinach; sauté 10-15 seconds and season with salt & pepper. remove from heat and sprinkle with parmesan.

introducing my favorite healthy + hearty INSTANT POT TURKEY PUMPKIN CHILI because mid-september says we’re headed straight for comfort food season, babyyy. 🎃👏🏻 this one’s thick and appropriately chunky, spicy with full-bodied flavor (but not so hot you can’t handle it), and excellently scoopable. (that’s the whole point of chili, right?!)

aaand not to mention it does that magic thing where it GETS BETTER AS LEFTOVERS. bless. 

the toppings: a heavenly salad bar of possibilities: avocado, cilantro, cheddar cheese, green onions, sour cream, crumbled corn bread…crushed fritos if you’re feeling classy.👌🏻♥️

HEALTHY & HEARTY INSTANT POT PUMPKIN CHILI
1 tbsp. olive oil • 1 cup onion, chopped • 1 green bell pepper, chopped • 3 cloves garlic • 1 lb. ground turkey • 1 (14oz) can diced tomatoes • 1 (14oz) can pumpkin • 1 (14oz) can kidney beans (drained) • 1 (14oz) can white beans (drained) • 2 tbsp. chili powder • 1 tsp. smoked paprika • 1 tsp cumin • ¼ tsp dried oregano • 1 tsp better than bouillon  seasoned vegetable base (dissolved in 8 oz boiling water) OR 1 cup chicken or vegetable broth 

toppings: greek yogurt or sour cream, cilantro, green onions, grated cheese, avocado, CRUMBLED CORN BREAD, crushed chips

1) in the saute mode,  cook onion, green pepper, and olive oil for 5 minutes. 2) add garlic and ground turkey; saute 5 min. 3) add all remaining ingredients to the instant pot. cook on high pressure for 15 minutes before releasing pressure.

node.text:
✨baked gnocchi marinara with basil and mozzarella! ✨🍅 this recipe is like guests on a friday night meets casual sweatpants meets date night dinner. it’s mega cozy with equal parts fancy + down-to-earth, and comes together in 20 minutes, leaving more time for wine + wind-down time. 👏🏻🥂 

here’s the thing: you could 100% make your gnocchi from scratch. but you could also do 70% of the homemade without hours of advanced gnocchi prep. I’m a big fan of option B because it requires less mixing + measuring and makes life easy while still keeping dinner delicious. 👌🏻🥰

BAKED GNOCCHI MARINARA w/ BASIL & MOZZARELLA

1 lb. potato gnocchi (I like delallo) OR 2 bags trader joe’s cauliflower gnocchi, cooked according to package directions • 1 (28 oz) crushed san marzano tomatoes• 2 garlic cloves, finely chopped • 1 large handful fresh basil • 8 oz fresh mozzarella chopped or torn (2 balls) • 1 tbsp olive oil • salt and pepper to taste 

1. preheat oven to 400 degrees.
2. heat olive oil in large skillet; add garlic and sauté for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant but not browned. 2) add canned tomatoes with a pinch of salt and pepper.  simmer sauce for ~5 minutes, then add half of the mozzarella and basil, stirring to combine. 3) add cooked gnocchi to tomato mixture and toss to coat. if your skillet isn’t oven proof, transfer to an oven-proof baking dish. 5) top gnocchi with remaining mozzarella and bake 20 minutes until the cheese is melted, bubbly, and golden!

cheesy garlic chicken fritters! ✨🍃🧄🍔 these mini burgs have been on repeat since I first made them last year and come loooaded with fresh herbs, melty mozz, and more garlic than should legally be allowed. 💥 I like to pair them with creamy cauliflower mash and grilled veg, but they’re also perf pattied between a bun or served atop a salad. aka enjoy however you want whenever you want! ♥️😘 

CHEESE & GARLIC CHICKEN FRITTERS: 1  pound ground chicken • 2 eggs • 1/3 cup almond flour • 1/2 cup grated parmsan • 1/2 cup grated mozzarella • 2 tablespoons fresh basil, chopped • 2 tablespoons fresh chives, chopped • 2 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder • salt and pepper, to taste. 1. mix all ingredients well, to combine. 2. heat 1/2 tablespoon avocado oil in large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. form 2-3-inch patties and transfer to pan. cook until brown on both sides, about 6-8 minutes.

CREAMY CAULIFLOWER MASH WITH GARLIC & PARMESAN: 1 head cauliflower, chopped • 3 garlic cloves • 3-4 tablespoons unsweetened almond milk • 1/4 cup parmesan cheese • 1-2 tablespoons ghee • 1) in a large pot with a steamer basket, steam garlic and cauliflower until tender; add to a food processor along with remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.

a thick slice of moist n’ fluffy PUMPKIN STREUSEL COFFEE CAKE to kick off wednesday the right waaayy. 🎉🧡 this one’s full-on fall (tell me you’re counting down the days without telling me you’re counting down the days 🍂) and loaded with warming spices + a crumbly streusel topping I could totally eat by the bowlful.  feel free to swap butter for coconut oil, and if you’re feeling feisty, toss some chocolate chips and toasted pecans into the batter. enjoy!! 🎃 

PUMPKIN STREUSEL COFFEE CAKE 
{gluten-free • grain-free • paleo-friendly • keto-adaptable}

1/2 cup canned pumpkin 
1/4 cup coconut oil, melted 
2 eggs 
1/2 tsp. vanilla 
1 cup almond flour 
1/3 cup coconut flour 
1/2 cup coconut sugar, sugar, or swerve granular
1/4 cup vanilla whey or egg white protein powder 
2 tsp. baking powder 
3/4 tsp. pumpkin pie spice 
1/4 tsp. salt 

streusel topping: 
1 cup almond flour 
1/4 cup coconut flour
1/2 cup brown sugar or swerve brown
1/2 tsp. pumpkin pie spice 
1/2 cup butter or coconut oil, melted 
1/4 tsp. salt 

1. combine wet ingredients in a small bowl (pumpkin through vanilla); whisk until smooth. 2) in a large bowl, combine dry ingredients (almond flour through salt). 3) stir wet ingredients into dry and whisk until fully incorporated. 4) pour into a greased 9x9” baking pan. 5) make streusel topping: combine all ingredients in a small bowl until crumble forms; sprinkle over cake batter. 6) bake at 325F. for 35-40 mins.

✨weeknight creamy kale cacio e pepe! ✨ the mood of this meal is simple + easy meets feels-a-little-bit-fancy, which is generally how I like to do life: not over-complicating but sprinkling in extras here and there while working in lots of wholesome ingredients (hiii, kale) and relying on quality convenience items when I need them. 

quality convenience items: this is where trader joe’s plays an integral role in liiifee! in this recipe, we visit the freezer aisle for cacio e pepe, then bring it home and toss it in a pan and with garlic (duh) and greens (nutrients 👏🏻). 

if you don’t have a trader joe’s near you, a from-scratch version of this recipe is in the comments. but regardless of whether you go 100% homemade or semi-homemade, this cacio e pepe pasta is saying hey hi hello I want to be on your table. 👋🏻♥️

CREAMY KALE CACIO E PEPE
(serves 2-3)
1 package trader joe’s cacio e pepe • 2 tsp. olive oil • 3 cloves garlic, minced • 3 cups finely shredded or chopped kale • 1/4 cup grated parmesan 

1. heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat for ~1 minute. add garlic and sauté 1-3 minutes; add kale and sauté an additional 3-4 minutes, or until wilted. 2) add 2 tablespoons water, plus the contents of the bag of cacio e pepe, to the pan, evenly nestling the noodle nests into the kale. cover and cook 5-6 minutes, or until noodles are tender. sprinke with parmesan and serve!

CREAMY KALE CACIO E PEPE (homemade version)

8 oz spaghetti, cooked ‘al dente,’ pasta water reserved (don’t toss it!) • 2 tsp salt • 2 tbsp. extra virgin olive oil • 1 tbsp. butter 2 tsp. fresh, coarsely ground black pepper • 3 cups finely chopped kale • 3/4 cup finely grated parmesan cheese 

1) heat a large sauté pan over medium heat. add olive oil, butter and freshly ground black pepper; stir until the butter melts and the pepper becomes fragrant; add kale and sauté 2-3 minutes, or until wilted 2) add 1 cup pasta water to the pepper/oil/butter mixture and stir to combine. toss in the hot pasta and add 1/2 cup of the cheese. continue cooking 2-3 more minutes, adding pasta water to create a creamy sauce. serve with remaining parmesan and parsley, if desired.

node.text:
pizza friday meets gameday snackurday meets let’s use up the rest of that summer squash 👏🏻🥒🏈🍕 

zucchini pizza bites are the answer when your heart says cheese but your head says veggies and require just four ingredients to quell those cravings while packing a glow-up of greens to boot. serve with netflix and wine because your weekend wants it. 😘 

ZUCCHINI PIZZA BITES 
(serves 1 but can be easily doubled)

1 zucchini
2-3 tablespoons tomato or pizza sauce (use your favorite!)
1/2 cup mozzarella, grated 
4-5 @applegate turkey pepperoni (I used a tiny cookie cutter to make minis, but they can be cut into strips or triangles if you don’t have one).
chopped parsley for garnish

1. slice zucchini into 1/2-inch rounds. top with sauce, mozzarella, and pepperoni. bake at 400 F for ~10 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly. garnish with chopped parsley!

node.text:
toasted cacio e pepe ravioli with crispy brussels, parmesan, & brown butterrr ✨🤩 this 15 minute meal calls for for just 5 ingredients and is the fastest way to take a grocery store staple (packaged pasta) from ordinary to extraordinary. 👏🏻 

fresh ravioli is crisped in a skillet and then  tossed with sauteed brussels, brown butter, parmesan, and toasted almonds. 👌🏻 extra pepper (pepe) optional -- but not for the faint of heart because this pasta packs a lil punch. 😘

1 package cacio e pepe ravioli, boiled according to package directions • 2 cups brussels sprouts leaves, separated • 1/4 cup shaved parmesan • 1/4 cup hazelnuts , roasted • 2-3 tablespoons butter • feta or goat cheese for garnish • salt & pepper, to taste 

1. to prepare the toasted ravioli, heat  2 teaspoons oil (I use avocado), in a large skillet. once hot, add ravioli and toast 1-2 minutes/side, or until slightly brown and crispy. 2. remove ravioli from pan and add butter; swirl around until slightly brown; add brussels sprouts and sauté a couple minutes, until wilted and slightly crispy. 3. add ravioli to brussels and toss. remove from heat and sprinkled with almonds and parmesan. season with salt & pepper to taste.

✨ one pan creamy garlic sundried tomato-basil shrimp! ✨ this little skillet sitch is so fast, so easy, so garlicky, so good. 👏🏻

you’ll need:

✔️shrimp 
✔️sundried tomatoes 
✔️spinach
✔️garlic
✔️parmesan
✔️basil
✔️cream or coconut cream 
✔️pantry spices 

pair with noodles, zoodles, or crusty bread (my fave) to sop up the sawcee. HAPPY SEPTEMBER! ♥️♥️

CREAMY GARLIC & SUNDRIED TOMATO-BASIL SHRIMP SKILLET
(gluten-free • grain-free • keto-friendly • dairy-free option)
 
1-2 tbsp. butter or ghee • 4 cloves garlic, minced • 1 lb. shrimp • 1 small onion, chopped • 1/2 cup white wine (optional) • 1/3 cup sun dried tomato strips in oil, drained • 1.5 cups unsweetened almond milk creamer OR half and half OR coconut cream • 3 cups spinach • 1/2 cup parmesan (or vegan parmesan), grated • 1 tbsp. fresh basil, chopped

directions will be posted in the comments! note: white wine can be omitted; there is not need to replace it with anything else.

manifesting crisp fall cozy sweater weather and comfort food meals like spaghetti squash alfredoooo! 🍽🥰 made this for dinner tonight (swipe to see exhibit b + c) and am currently curled up on the couch with no intentions to move unless it’s to serve myself seconds. 

it’s been sooo hot + humid in DC the past few weeks, and even though summer is my season, I’ve never been more ready for fall — the flavors, the foliage, the PIES (!!). hope everyone had a great monday and also hope you makethismakethismakethis. 😘

SPAGHETTI SQUASH ALFREDO
(gluten-free • dairy-free ) 

1 spaghetti squash, roasted • 1/2 cup cream cheese (dairy-free or regular )
1/4 cup parmesan cheese • 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk, warmed in the microwave 1 minute • 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder • 1/4 teaspoon white pepper (or regular pepper) + a dash of salt, to taste

1) remove squash strands from spaghetti squash; place half in a large bowl and save the rest for later 2) in a blender combine all remaining ingredients, except parsley. blend until smooth. toss with hot spaghetti squash and garnish with parsley. serve with pan-seared chicken breast (optional).
